Something of an accidental psi-link with Azron Gurdon has left Bucky wondering if there isn’t more going on than meets the eye. Constantly searching for clues to uncover the true nature of things.  Has become somewhat aware of the Enclosure.  But is nervous about discussing any of this with others.   Is beginning to realize that something, some one (the Agency) is monitoring him.
Intensely attracted to Birakay, as many young people are, but to a fairly obsessive degree. Gets a big boner when listening to Birakay songs being sung. Not sure what this means or what to do about it.
Often dreams (literally) about mechanisms for virtual dynamic visual presentation (i.e., film, animation, video, streaming, etc.) —  a type of technology that, like flight, is utterly unheard-of in the world of Mantemar.  This intersects with Bucky’s obsession over Birakay, but also leads to problems in communicating with others, who tend to deride such ideas as foolishness or madness.
External Conflicts
Many funny/annoying struggles with Beaverton Guild bureaucracy, maybe reminiscent a little bit of Kafka’s kind of deadpan humor. 
The Jaxen have instructions to terminate Bucky if knowledge of their collective plans gets too exposed; meanwhile they cultivate Bucky as a potential agent, sending operatives his way as honey pots of various kinds trying to understand what is known, how they might manipulate to their advantage.

Notes

